  "title": "CNC Lathe Machinist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>Specialize in gear manufacturing. Provide engineering solution for various industries. Machining & fabrication works. Engineering solutions provider.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will program and operate CNC lathe machines to produce precision mechanical parts, applying engineering problem-solving skills to ensure quality and efficiency. Collaborate within a self-managed, horizontal organization to deliver innovative machining and fabrication solutions.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Program CNC lathe machines to manufacture mechanical components according to specifications</li><li>Operate CNC lathe machines to produce parts with precision and efficiency</li><li>Utilize CAD and CAM software (Mastercam) to design and prepare machining processes for manufacturing</li><li>Use measuring tools to inspect parts and verify dimensional conformity to quality standards</li><li>Operate lifting cranes safely to handle heavy materials and components during machining processes</li><li>Perform reverse engineering to replicate mechanical parts accurately for production or repair</li><li>Analyze and solve engineering problems related to machining and fabrication to optimize processes</li><li>Collaborate autonomously within a horizontal organizational structure emphasizing self-management</li></ul>",
